        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 8:07PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 806 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Haynes, or 7 miles north of Marianna, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Marianna, Hughes, Haynes, Brickeys, New Home, Cody, Kokomo, Westor,
Jonquil, Mud Lake, Soudan, Peters, Council, Beck, Bruins, Democrat,
Heustess, North Hughes, Ball Point, and Lucerne.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
